## üéØ Overview

This repository showcases hands-on Docker learning with real-world applications:

- ‚úÖ **Containerizing Node.js & Python applications**
- ‚úÖ **Implementing bind mounts** for live development
- ‚úÖ **Optimizing Docker images** with best practices
- ‚úÖ **Git-to-Docker automation** workflows
- ‚úÖ **Multi-language containerization**

**Skills Demonstrated:**
- Dockerfile creation & optimization
- Docker networking & port mapping
- Volume management (bind mounts)
- Environment variable handling
- Multi-stage builds concepts
- Container lifecycle management

---

## üöÄ Projects

### 1. Basic Node.js Server

**üìÅ Location:** `/Basic_node_server`

A containerized Express.js REST API demonstrating fundamental Docker concepts.

**Features:**
- Simple REST endpoint (`/home`)
- Environment-based configuration
- Nodemon for auto-reload
- Optimized layer caching

**Quick Start:**
```bash
cd Basic_node_server
docker build -t node-basic-server .
docker run -p 3000:3000 node-basic-server
```

**Test:** `curl http://localhost:3000/home`

---

### 2. Bind Mount Demo

**üìÅ Location:** `/node-bind-mount-demo`

Demonstrates **live code synchronization** between host and container using bind mounts.

**Why Bind Mounts?**
- ‚ùå **Problem:** Rebuilding images after every code change is slow
- ‚úÖ **Solution:** Bind mounts sync local code directly into container
- üéØ **Result:** Edit code locally, see changes instantly!

**Run with Bind Mount:**
```bash
cd node-bind-mount-demo
docker build -t node-bind-demo .

# Linux/Mac
docker run -p 3000:3000 -v $(pwd):/app node-bind-demo

# Windows PowerShell
docker run -p 3000:3000 -v ${PWD}:/app node-bind-demo

# Windows CMD
docker run -p 3000:3000 -v %cd%:/app node-bind-demo
```

**Try It:** Edit `index.js` and see live updates without rebuilding!

---

### 3. Python Flask Server

**üìÅ Location:** `/python-server` *(if you have this)*

Containerized Python Flask application showing multi-language Docker skills.

**Quick Start:**
```bash
cd python-server
docker build -t python-flask-server .
docker run -p 5000:5000 python-flask-server
```

---

### 4. GitHub Integration

**üìÅ Location:** `/node_from_github`

**Advanced:** Automatically clone and containerize applications from GitHub.

**Dockerfile:**
```dockerfile
FROM node:18-alpine
WORKDIR /app
RUN apk add --no-cache git
RUN git clone https://github.com/narayannikhil/Dockerizing_node_project-.git .
ENV PORT=3000
RUN npm ci
CMD ["npm", "start"]
```

**Build & Run:**
```bash
docker build -t app-from-github .
docker run -p 3001:3000 app-from-github
```

**Use Case:** Deploy any Node.js app from GitHub with a single command!

---

## üìã Prerequisites

**Required:**
```bash
# Docker
docker --version  # Docker 20.10+

# Git
git --version

# Optional (for local testing)
node --version    # Node 18+
python --version  # Python 3.8+
```

**Install Docker:**
- **Windows/Mac:** [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop)
- **Linux:** 
  ```bash
  sudo apt-get update
  sudo apt-get install docker.io
  sudo systemctl start docker
  sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
  ```

